# Community Alerts — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development.
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHY NO NEXT_PUBLIC_ PREFIX?
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars are baked into the client-side JS bundle at `next build`.
# That means any Docker image built without them (or with wrong values) will
# forever call the wrong URLs — even if you update container env vars later.
#
# Instead, these vars are read by next.config.js at server startup to configure
# API proxy rewrites. The browser never sees backend URLs directly; it only ever
# calls /api-proxy/java/..., /api-proxy/ml/..., /api-proxy/notif/... on the
# same origin, and Next.js forwards the requests server-side.
#
# Set these as Environment Variables in your Azure Container App (not build args).
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Java Spring Boot API
JAVA_API_URL=http://localhost:8080

# Python ML API (FastAPI)
ML_API_URL=http://localhost:8001

# .NET Notification API
NOTIF_API_URL=http://localhost:5001
